title: For Sale/Trade:  Smith and Wesson Model 59...1st ever double stack S&W
postcontent: SMITH COLLECTORS ALERT!!! Smith and Wesson Model 59 9mm, the first ever Smith double stack 14 round automatic made from 1971 to 1981 and this one is nickle plate and very very good condition with no discoloration or peeling of the plating, no corrosion. Only very light surface handling marks and no scratches, grips are near perfect and shiny screws, bore is bright and average internal wear from a 37 year old gun. Comes with one original 14 rd. mag and a second with the thicker base plate plus a hard case, not the original. Extra mags are easy to find and cheap. I fired one mag through it for a function test and it shot great but haven't had a chance to set up targets and probably won't. The very first runs of these in the early years of production saw some issues with feeding different ammos and jamming, this is one of the last runs, serial in the A 6XX,XXX numbers made around 1980 or 1981 so doubtful it would ever have any of those problems. This gun is still highly collectable and in this condition getting harder to find. Wish I could keep it but family health issues, so it has to go. Price is 600 obo or a trade of equal value.
